<title>GREECE: BEFORE THE BELL - SHARES TRADING EX-DIVIDEND.</title>
<headline>BEFORE THE BELL - SHARES TRADING EX-DIVIDEND.</headline>
<dateline>ATHENS 1997-06-19</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares of Themeliodomi, Alte, Aluminium of Attica and Radio Korasidis will trade ex-dividend, the Athens stock exchange said in a statement.</p>
<p>The dividends per share have as follows:</p>
<p>    Themeliodomi		  130  drachmas</p>
<p>    Alte			    110</p>
<p>    Aluminium of Attica	  75</p>
<p>    Radio Korasidis	     100</p>
<p>Also on Thursday, shares of AB Vasilopoulos and Aluminium of Attica trade with a new, higher, par value -- 500 and 640 drachmas respectively.</p>
<p>Shares of ETBA Leasing trade ex-dividend and ex-bonus. The company's dividend per share for 1996 was 300 drachmas. The bonus issue calls for three bonus shares per 10 outstanding.</p>
<p>Piraeus Bank rights also start trading on Thursday, 8.4 million rights will start at a price of 1,806 drachmas. They expire July 18.</p>
<p>Adjusted starting prices will have as follows:</p>
<p>    Aluminium of Attica	   2,785   drachmas</p>
<p>    Radio Korasidis		 3,380</p>
<p>    Alte				3,730</p>
<p>    Themeliodomi		    3,310</p>
<p>    ETBA Leasing		    3,227</p>
<p>--George Georgiopoulos, Athens Newsroom +301 3311812-4</p>
